President Obama has nominated seven individuals to serve as U.S. Marshals. The nominees are Charles Edward Andrews for the Southern District of Alabama, Darrell James Bell for the District of Montana, William Benedict Berger Sr. for the Middle District of Florida, Russel Edwin Burger for the District of Oregon, Joseph Campbell Moore for the District of Wyoming, Edwin Donovan Sloane for the District of Columbia, and Esteban Soto III for the Superior Court for the District of Columbia. These nominees have extensive law enforcement experience and have demonstrated a strong commitment to public service.